I did Venril Sathir yesterday, so might as well post here now though the post is a bit old...

We did it with about 4 groups of lvl 50+ ppl, maybe a bit less, about 20 ppl.. But it cant be done with less..

The trick is to have a lvl 60+ tank with about 6K hp, and at least 3 chanters with Rune 5, and at least 2 clerics with CH...

The prep room in KC need to be cleared, and you need an FD puller to clear ANY adds from VS room... (If VS aggroes before room is clear, FD need to just stand and die, if VS aggroes the rest of the raiding party you will, and i repeat, you WILL ALL die!

When VS room is clear, MT need to be fully buffed and have Rune 5 up... No need in buffing everyone else cos' if ANYONE else than MT gets aggro you WILL ALL die!

MT attacks VS and builds aggro, with 3 chanters Chain Rune 5 him... VS procs 1500 lifetap VERY VERY often, but with Rune he wont get any life back, just tap the runes... So Rune 5 is even more important than CH, and without it VS cant be done!

3-4 patch healers like shammies, druids will be good as they chain cast 3-400hp heals on MT, which wont get aggro, and will save him if a CH lands too late! Clerics cast CH randomly with a 5 second interval! CH shouldnt be needed if Chain runing, but it should be done for safety reasons!

Tank should use 5+ secs to get aggro and then call assist! It is VERY important tank have aggro, cos' if VS bounces and starts attacking others his procs will heal him instantly and you will all die!

When tank calls aggro every melee jump in (You should have about 14 melees+)...

When VS is at about 40% health ALL wizzies nuke him with Lure spells like Lure of Flame.. You MUST use lure spells cos' they cant be resisted... VS will resist all other nukes and it will be useless.. When Wizzies Chain cast lure spells VS should go down in a few seconds...

If the fight lasts longer than 30-45 seconds, or MT dies you will get wipe!


This was done yesterday, and it worked like a charm with only one Necro casualty cos' he had pet on VS in front of him!

Plan this good, and you will get VS easily... You're welcome to e-mail me with questions

Regards...

